WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Real borscht takes a while to prepare. But it's worth it.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:36.000
Borscht begins with soup broth. Brown the meat and bones in an oven, pour water into the pot, and cook over low heat until boiling.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:01:02.000
Then add the onion, carrot, garlic, and a bouquet of aromatic herbs and spices. Let the flavor become saturated over medium heat for 2-3 hours. 

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:22.000
That is enough time to prepare all the other ingredients. Bake or boil the beet in its skin for 30-40 minutes.

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.333
Chop up the cabbage, onions, and potatoes, and grate the carrots.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Strain the broth and slice the meat from the bones.

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:11.000
The cabbage goes first.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:26.000
Fry the onions and carrots until soft and golden brown and a potent and full-bodied aroma fills the air. Add the onions and carrots to the broth, along with the potatoes.

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:45.000
